text: Anna Plyusova (born 10 September 1992) is an Uzbekistani water polo player. She was a member of the Uzbekistan women's national water polo team. She was a part of the team at the 2009 World Aquatics Championships, 2011 World Aquatics Championships, 2013 World Aquatics Championships, and 2010 Asian Games. == References == == Other websites == * Anna Plyusova of Uzbekistan is challenged by Anna Turova of Kazakhstan in the Women's Water Polo Semifinals Getty Category:1992 births Category:Uzbekistani water polo players Category:Living people
